BKNG<-read.csv("~/Desktop/560/560-website/data_scource/stock_price_data/BKNG_d.csv")
BKNG$Date=as.Date(BKNG$Date)
#log_Close<-log(ts_Adj.Close) # log transformation
data<-data.frame(BKNG$Date,BKNG$Adj.Close)
colnames(data)<-c("Date", "Adj.Close")
ts_Adj.Close<-ts(BKNG$Adj.Close,start=decimal_date(as.Date("2020-12-10")),frequency = 253)
#ts_Adj.Close<-ma(ts_Adj.Close,7)
# TS plot
autoplot(ts_Adj.Close)

# ACF plot
acf(ts_Adj.Close)

#Lag plot
gglagplot(ts_Adj.Close, do.lines = F, set.lags = c(1,4,8,12)) #lag =1

log_Close<-log(ts_Adj.Close) # log transformation
#D=1 Do a seasonal differencing with lag=12 to remove the seasonality
log_Close %>% diff(lag=12) %>%
  ggtsdisplay(xlab="Year",
              main="Seasonality differenced BKNG Close Price")

# Do an ordinary differencing to make the series stationary
log_Close %>% diff(lag=12) %>%diff() %>%
  ggtsdisplay(xlab="Year",
              main='Seasonally&Ordinary differenced BKNG Stock Price')

# Determine (p,d,q)x(P,D,Q) and evaluate model
#Fit sarima(0,1,0)x(1,1,3)
fit=sarima(log_Close,0,1,0,1,1,3,12)

Cross Validation using 1 step

k<-50 # minimum data length for fitting a model
n<-length(ts_Adj.Close) #data length for testing the model
n-k
## [1] 249
i=1
err1 = c()
err2 = c()

for (i in 1:(n-k)) {
  xtrain <- ts_Adj.Close[1:(k-1)+1]
  xtest <- ts_Adj.Close[k+i]
  
  fit<-Arima(xtrain, order = c(0,1,0), include.drift = TRUE, method = "ML")
  fcast1 <- forecast(fit, h=1)
  
  fit2<-Arima(xtrain, order = c(1,1,3), include.drift = TRUE, method = "ML")
  fcast2 <-forecast(fit2, h=1)
  
  err1 = c(err1, abs(fcast1$mean-xtest))
  err2 = c(err2, abs(fcast2$mean-xtest))
}
mean(err1) #102
## [1] 102.0791
mean(err2) #103
## [1] 103.9591
farimal <- function(x,h){forecast(Arima(x, order = c(1,1,3)), h=h)}

# compute cv errors for 1 step
e <- tsCV(ts_Adj.Close, forecastfunction = farimal, h=1)
